article.headline: TCU 47, Navy 45
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Devonta Abron had 13 points and 12 rebounds in his first start at TCU as the Horned Frogs defeated Navy 47-45 Tuesday night. Abron didn't attempt a field goal in the first half but then made five of six shots in the second half and was instrumental in the Frogs turning around a game with nine ties and nine lead changes. A transfer from Arkansas, Abron led the Razorbacks in rebounding as a true freshman last season before being granted an NCAA waiver to be eligible to play this season. TCU (4-1) has held four of its first five opponents to fewer than 50 points. Worth Smith scored 14 points and Brandon Venturini had 12 points for Navy (2-3).
